author: gstein
msg: Stop constructing a baton, and just pass parameters. There are no
callbacks here where the baton is needed.
* subversion/libsvn_client/externals.c:
(struct external_change_baton_t): removed.
(switch_file_external): remove unused TIMESTAMP_SLEEP param
(handle_external_item_removal): take a CTX rather than a baton.
adjust internals.
(handle_external_item_change): take a CTX, REPOS_ROOT_URL, and
TIMESTAMP_SLEEP params rather than a baton. adjust internals.
(wrap_external_error): take a CTX rather than a baton.
(handle_externals_change): take CTX, REPOS_ROOT_URL, and
TIMESTAMP_SLEEP params rather than a baton.
(svn_client__handle_externals): stop constructing a baton, and just
pass the parameters as appropriate.
(svn_client__export_externals): stop constructing a baton, and just
pass CTX to the error wrapper.
